### Bug #8 — Yellow Signal Auto-Clears to Green (MINOR)

**File:** [railway_environment.py](file:///home/asml-7200u/Desktop/project/railway_controller/server/railway_environment.py#L948-L954)

```python
if current_seg.signal_state == SignalState.YELLOW:
    train.status = TrainStatus.WAITING
    train.speed = 0.5
    current_seg.signal_state = SignalState.GREEN  # ← Auto-clears!
```

If the agent sets a signal to YELLOW, it automatically becomes GREEN next step (the train "waits 1 step then proceeds"). But YELLOW is also set automatically when a block ahead is occupied (line 974). This creates a race condition where the agent's intentional YELLOW gets overridden or the automatic YELLOW gets auto-cleared.

