### Bug #9 — `_get_delay_status` Regex Match on Status Strings is Fragile

**File:** [railway_environment.py](file:///home/asml-7200u/Desktop/project/railway_controller/server/railway_environment.py#L797-L799)

```python
"recommendations": [
    t for t in train_delays 
    if t["status"] in ["running_late", "critical_time"] or t["is_held"]
][:3],
```

The status strings like `"running_late ({current_delay} steps)"` contain dynamic content. The filter checks for exact match `"running_late"` which will **never match** because the actual value is `"running_late (3 steps)"`. The recommendations list will always be empty unless a train is held.

**Fix:** Use `t["status"].startswith("running_late")` instead.

