### Bug #10 — Basic Network Route Mismatch

**File:** [railway_environment.py](file:///home/asml-7200u/Desktop/project/railway_controller/server/railway_environment.py#L259-L299)

The basic network has segments `A-J1`, `J1-CROSS`, `J1-B`, `D-J1`, `J1-C`. 
- `A-J1` has `next_segments=["J1-B"]` — this means A-J1 connects directly to J1-B, skipping J1-CROSS.
- But T1's route is `["A-J1", "J1-CROSS", "J1-B"]`.

The `next_segments` graph doesn't match the assigned routes. This means `_calculate_route()` (BFS) would find a *different* path than the hardcoded route. If anyone calls `route_train()`, the recalculated route will skip J1-CROSS entirely, and the trains will never conflict — defeating the purpose of the task.

**Fix:** `A-J1` should have `next_segments=["J1-CROSS"]` and `D-J1` should have `next_segments=["J1-CROSS"]`. Similarly `J1-CROSS` correctly has `next_segments=["J1-B", "J1-C"]`.

