### Bug #11 — `try/except ImportError` Is Useless

**Files:** [app.py](file:///home/asml-7200u/Desktop/project/railway_controller/server/app.py#L14-L19), [railway_environment.py](file:///home/asml-7200u/Desktop/project/railway_controller/server/railway_environment.py#L26-L31)

```python
try:
    from openenv.core.env_server.mcp_environment import MCPEnvironment
    from openenv.core.env_server.types import Action, Observation, State
except ImportError:
    from openenv.core.env_server.mcp_environment import MCPEnvironment  # Same!
    from openenv.core.env_server.types import Action, Observation, State
```

Both branches are identical. If the import fails, the except will fail with the same error.

